lly like a ball. The more seawater it swallows, the higher it bounces."},{"version":"soulsilver","text":"It bounces playfully like a ball. The more seawater it swallows, the higher it bounces."},{"version":"black","text":"On sunny days, it lands on beaches to bounce like a ball and play. It spouts water from its nose."},{"version":"white","text":"On sunny days, it lands on beaches to bounce like a ball and play. It spouts water from its nose."},{"version":"black-2","text":"It eats one ton of food every day. It plays by shooting stored seawater out its blowholes with great force."},{"version":"white-2","text":"It eats one ton of food every day. It plays by shooting stored seawater out its blowholes with great force."},{"version":"x","text":"It bounces playfully like a ball. The more seawater it swallows, the higher it bounces."},{"version":"y","text":"It eats one ton of food every day. It plays by shooting stored seawater out its blowholes with great force."},{"version":"omega-ruby","text":"Wailmer\u2019s nostrils are located above its eyes. This playful Pok\u00e9mon loves to startle people by forcefully snorting out seawater it stores inside its body out of its nostrils."},{"version":"alpha-sapphire","text":"Wailmer can store water inside its body to transform itself into a ball for bouncing around on the ground. By filling itself up with more water, this Pok\u00e9mon can elevate the height of its bounces."},{"version":"sun","text":"It loves to startle people. It fills itself up with seawater and plays by bouncing around like a ball."},{"version":"moon","text":"It shows off by spraying jets of seawater from the nostrils above its eyes. It eats a solid ton of Wishiwashi every day."},{"version":"ultra-sun","text":"It swims along with its mouth open and swallows down seawater along with its food. It sprays excess water out of its nostrils."},{"version":"ultra-moon","text":"Due to their memories of when they once lived on land, pods of them will, very rarely, wash up on